flowchart TD
  A[Trigger: Scheduled planning run (e.g., daily/weekly) or event-trigger (container shortage, overdue returns, inbound schedule change).]
  A --> N1[Stream: STREAMS - Consolidate master and transaction data from SAP and partner systems]
  N1 --> N2[Cortex: Subject Areas - Prepare network model and inputs for optimization]
  N2 --> N3[Cortex: Remote Functions - Run deterministic optimization solver and business-rule filters]
  N3 --> N4{PB: Process Builder - Apply approval rules and route exceptions}
  N4 -->|Primary| N5[PB: Remote Functions - Execute approved schedule and notify execution systems and carriers]
  N5 --> N6[PB: UI Screen - Surface plan and KPIs to planners; allow overrides where necessary]
  N6 --> Z1[Outcome: Reduced container transport COGS, faster container turnover (lower days outstanding), improved OTIF and supplier receipt compliance, and fewer manual planning interventions.]
  N4 -->|Optimization improvement configured...| B1[Skip automated replan; mark for periodic review and retain current schedule]
  B1 --> O1[Outcome: Avoid churn; maintain stability when changes provide minimal benefit]
  O1 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Carrier capacity or transit constrain...| B2[Process Builder opens CWB Lifecycle exceptions and triggers fallback routing heuristic]
  B2 --> O2[Outcome: Partial automated replan applied; unresolved items routed to planners for manual assignment]
  O2 --> End[End]
  N4 -->|Supplier non-compliance (overdue retu...| B3[Raise compliance exception CWB, notify supplier via Supplier Portal integration, and apply contractual penalties per rules]
  B3 --> O3[Outcome: Supplier engagement and corrective action; contested items held in exception until resolved]
  O3 --> End[End]
  Z1 --> End[End]